<p>1893-May-25</p>
<p>ESR to EDA</p>
<p>{{PB}}</p>
<p>{{DATELINE}} Boston, May 25, 1893</p>
<p>{{SALUTE}} My dear Mr Atkinson</p>
<p>If you could stop in </p>
<p>on Saturday morning on your </p>
<p>way to the office I </p>
<p>could show you some bulky </p>
<p>things to better advantage </p>
<p>than to bring them - You </p>
<p>have never seen Egleston's </p>
<p>vegetables. </p>
<p>No - I must not put the </p>
<p>Aladdin on the back of these </p>
<p>menus. I want [a lot] of the </p>
<p>circulars to have with the </p>
<p>oven. And I had thought </p>
<p>of a short leaflet of four</p>
<p>{{PB}}<lb/>pages setting forth the </p>
<p>object of the whole exhibit. </p>
<p>Something like the enclosed. </p>
<p>Perhaps you will have an </p>
<p>idea for me. I do not </p>
<p>wish to give away a great </p>
<p>[man] of stuff. These little </p>
<p>menus are only given with </p>
<p>the lunch.</p>
<p>I shall have several </p>
<p>order books, one for the </p>
<p>oven one for science of </p>
<p>nutrition &amp;c. </p>
<p>{{CLOSE}} Yours truly</p>
<p>{{SIGNED}} Ellen H. Richards</p>
<p>If you are not busy please get up </p>
<p>your leaflet - out of the McClure </p>
<p>papers.</p>
<p>[page 3, notes]</p>
<p>German work -</p>
<p>American work -</p>
<p>Atwater </p>
<p>Science of nutrition</p>
<p>The New England Kitchen</p>
<p>An account of which is </p>
<p>published printed in the </p>
<p>Story of the kitchen</p>
<p>142 Pleasant St </p>
<p>Boston</p>
<p>341 Hudson St </p>
<p>N.Y.</p>
<p>335 So Halsted St </p>
<p>Chicago</p>
<p>The Aladdin Oven </p>
<p>Made by Kenswick Bros</p>
<p>Brookline Mass</p>
<p>[page 4, notes]	</p>
<p>The Rumford Inn</p>
<p>Its Object –</p>
<p>1 To awaken new interest </p>
<p>in what Count Rumford </p>
<p>called 100 years ago </p>
<p>called the Science of </p>
<p>Nutrition.</p>
<p>2 To place on record </p>
<p>some of the work </p>
<p>already accomplished</p>
<p>3 To point out lines for</p>
<p>further work.</p>
<p> </p>
